Application-based segmentation further highlights the versatility of CNS stimulants in addressing various neurological conditions. ADHD emerges as a key driver of market demand, given its prevalence among children and adults worldwide. The effective management of ADHD symptoms through stimulant medications underscores the importance of continued research and development in this area. Narcolepsy, characterized by excessive daytime sleepiness and sudden muscle weakness, presents another significant application for CNS stimulants. The market's response to the treatment needs of individuals with narcolepsy reflects the growing awareness and recognition of sleep disorders as a public health concern.

